 his economic manuscripts, historic writings, notebooks of excerpts, and letters, of which many were only published recently in the Marx-Engels-Gesamtausgabe. Marx did not want to merely explain the recurrence of crises; he also wanted to understand how and why they change the world.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aKapitalismus. 4aKrisentheorie. 4aMarx, Karl. 4aWirtschaftsgeschichte. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aMarx, Karl.  acapitalism.  acrisis theory.  aeconomic history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831107451220 cprintz978311074493440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074502340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110745023423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110745023/original  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPHb2022